cs.CV, cs.MM, cs.IR, cs.CL, cs.LG 

The paper focuses on visual sentiment analysis, which involves analyzing emotions and sentiments from visual content such as images and videos. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also involves machine learning and deep learning techniques, which are commonly used in the sub-categories of cs.MM (Multimedia) and cs.IR (Information Retrieval). Additionally, the paper discusses natural language processing techniques, which are relevant to the sub-category of cs.CL (Computation and Language). Finally, the paper proposes a deep visual sentiment analyzer, which falls under the sub-category of cs.LG (Machine Learning).
